-- Spain's Bankinter posts 31 pct H1 profit growth
-- 
-- Thu Jul 24, 2014 02:15AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, July 24 (Reuters) - Mid-sized Spanish lender Bankinter <BKT.MC> on Thursday posted a 31 percent rise in first half net profit from a year ago, building on a recovery in revenues as the country emerges from recession.

Bankinter, Spain's seventh largest bank by market value, said profit was 134 million euros ($180 million) in the period, beating analyst forecasts of 126 million euros in a Reuters poll.